<br>
Graphics, kick ass no doubt. Voice acting is pretty good. I love Auron's and Rikku's voice. Everyone else in the party is suitable, Tidus is iffy at times, but does the trick.<br>
<br>
But what really kills me is the story. It sucks. I mean what is the point? It didn't seem epic to me at all, and there were huge chunks of the game where I had to drag myself through it. For most of the game you're accompanying Yuna on a pilgrimage. Whoop dee doo. This game has nothing to the depth of the stories of IV, VI, VII, Chrono Trigger, Xenogears or even FFTactics! Those were games that truly had epic story lines with multiple plot twists. I found FFX to be extremely predictable.<br>
<br>
And hey, no offense guys, but how in the world can you say FFX had the best character development? It practically had none! You've got Wakka, the dumb jock who talks annoying as crap; Lulu the chick with huge breasts who casts spells; Yuna, the healer/summoner who is emotionless as crap and must go on a magic pilgrimmage for aeons; and Tidus, the naive protagonist who says inspiring things like, &quot;Yeah!&quot; and &quot;Let's go!&quot; and who you know is going to fall for Yuna since the first time you see her. The only two characters I actually like are Auron, who is pretty bad ass because he is mysterious and @#%$, and Rikku, because whoever played her voice captured her perfectly and it honestly makes me smile. And oh yeah, I forgot Kimahri- but what does that matter, so does the game! He might as well not exist half the time! Every character is cast into die-hard roles and they don't deviate period. They are all, with the rare exception of Auron, extremely predictable, extremely shallow, and extremely boring!<br>
<br>
Now that I'm started, let me get going on what is quite possibly the worst enemy in all of RPG history, Seymour. First off, why the hell did they name him Seymour?! My god, that doesn't inspire fear or evilness at all. I keep thinking of Seymour in the Simpsons! Not to mention his voice- Jesus H. Christ, start up the pink pride parades? He is such a pansy ass villain. <br>
<br>
In short, this story sucks because there are no heroes, there are no villains, no humanity, no fall from grace- just a bunch of attractive people running around doing innane little quests to beat &quot;Sin.&quot; Yay.<br>
<br>
Say what you want, but FFX in league with the greats? Hell no. It's a good game to kill sometime, but it sure isn't a masterpiece. Square has really lost it's touch: FFVIII-FFX, Chrono Cross... it's a shame = / <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urasplorien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rasplorien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Shadowed Man</span><br>  Posts: 231<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/6/02 8:50:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5764.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: owns</span><hr size=1> The story reminded me a lot of Xenogears for some reason... the &quot;fake religion&quot; and stuff... Hell, even Sin LOOKED a little like the Xenogears when he grew those wings at the battle where you fought his mouth hehe.<br>
<br>
The stroy was a little lacking, but it was still a good game imo.  I wish it was explained more about the war that created Tidus' Zanarkan.<br>
<br>
This was also Square's first game using voices and whatnot, so perhaps it's a warmup to FF11 =) one can hope.  It was somewhat epic... defeating an endless cycle of death.  As for Seymor, his name could have been more evil, but the voice you hear is that of one who is insane... and being around insane people sometimes, I know :-) If he had a deep evil voice, would you really be led to believe that he would have the power, or intentions, of destroying the world? Look at Kefka... I'm sure if he had a voice, it would be even worse.<br>
<br>
